#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.15"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.15:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.15:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. Childless "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.15:0.3"
msgid "15. Dutiyasaṅgāmasutta "
msgstr "15. Battle (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.84, pts2ed1.190, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.15:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ abbhuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr "Then King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha mobilized an army of four divisions and marched to Kāsi to attack King Pasenadi of Kosala. "

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.2"
msgid "Assosi kho rājā pasenadi kosalo: "
msgstr "When King Pasenadi heard of this, "

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.3"
msgid "“rājā kira māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā mamaṃ abbhuyyāto yena kāsī”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ paccuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr "he mobilized an army of four divisions and marched to Kāsi to defend it against Ajātasattu. "

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho rājā ca māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājā ca pasenadi kosalo saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then the two kings met in battle. "

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.6"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana saṅgāme rājā pasenadi kosalo rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ parājesi, jīvaggāhañca naṃ aggahesi. "
msgstr "And in that battle Pasenadi defeated Ajātasattu and captured him alive. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.15:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi thought, "

msgctxt "sn3.15:1.8"
msgid "“kiñcāpi kho myāyaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto adubbhantassa dubbhati, atha ca pana me bhāgineyyo hoti. "
msgstr "“Even though I’ve never betrayed this King Ajātasattu, he betrayed me. Still, he is my nephew. "

# NOTE: I don’t think BB’s “confiscated” can work. What does it mean, Pasenadi marched home with all Ajatasattu’s troops? I don’t think so. Normally pariyadiyati means overpowered, mastered, vanquished, and so it means here.
#. VAR: osajjeyyan”ti → ossajjeyyanti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn3.15:1.9"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno vedehiputtassa sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ rathakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ osajjeyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Now that I’ve vanquished all of Ajātasattu’s elephant troops, cavalry, chariots, and infantry, why don’t I let him loose with just his life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: osajji → ossajji (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn3.15:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno vedehiputtassa sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ rathakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ osajji. "
msgstr "And that’s what he did. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn3.15:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then several mendicants … "

msgctxt "sn3.15:3.2"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "told the Buddha what had happened. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.85, pts2ed1.192, sc4
msgctxt "sn3.15:4.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhante, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ abbhuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.2"
msgid "Assosi kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.3"
msgid "‘rājā kira māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā mamaṃ abbhuyyāto yena kāsī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ paccuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.5"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, rājā ca māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājā ca pasenadi kosalo saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.6"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhante, saṅgāme rājā pasenadi kosalo rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ parājesi, jīvaggāhañca naṃ aggahesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.8"
msgid "‘kiñcāpi kho myāyaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto adubbhantassa dubbhati, atha ca pana me bhāgineyyo hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.15:4.9"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno vedehiputtassa sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ sabbaṃ rathakāyaṃ sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ osajjeyyan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.15:5.1"
msgid "“Atha kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo rañño māgadhassa ajātasattuno vedehiputtassa sabbaṃ hatthikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ assakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ rathakāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā sabbaṃ pattikāyaṃ pariyādiyitvā jīvantameva naṃ osajjī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn3.15:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.193, sc7
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.1"
msgid "“Vilumpateva puriso, "
msgstr "“A man goes on plundering "

# NOTE: This and AN 10.177 seem to be the only occurrences of this verb in the EBTs, apart from the causative form in DN 15.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.2"
msgid "yāvassa upakappati; "
msgstr "as long as it serves his ends. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.3"
msgid "Yadā caññe vilumpanti, "
msgstr "But as soon as others plunder him, "

# NOTE: See BB for this line.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: viluppati → vilumpati (si, s1-3, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.15:7.4"
msgid "so vilutto viluppati. "
msgstr "the plunderer is plundered. "

# NOTE: The use of thana here is obscure; BB has fortuneis on his side. I relate it to use the use of thana as “possible”, i.e. they can do it, i.e. they can get away with it.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.1"
msgid "Ṭhānañhi maññati bālo, "
msgstr "For the fool thinks they’ve got away with it "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.2"
msgid "yāva pāpaṃ na paccati; "
msgstr "as long as the wickedness doesn’t ripen. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.3"
msgid "Yadā ca paccati pāpaṃ, "
msgstr "But when the wickedness ripens, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:8.4"
msgid "atha dukkhaṃ nigacchati. "
msgstr "they fall into suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: labhati → labhati hantā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.1"
msgid "Hantā labhati hantāraṃ, "
msgstr "A killer creates a killer; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.2"
msgid "jetāraṃ labhate jayaṃ; "
msgstr "a conqueror creates a conqueror; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.3"
msgid "Akkosako ca akkosaṃ, "
msgstr "an abuser creates abuse, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.4"
msgid "rosetārañca rosako; "
msgstr "and a bully creates a bully. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.5"
msgid "Atha kammavivaṭṭena, "
msgstr "And so as deeds unfold "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.15:9.6"
msgid "so vilutto viluppatī”ti. "
msgstr "the plunderer is plundered.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
